WEBVTT

00:05.070 --> 00:07.459
[ British accent ] I KNOW
YOU SAID A LA'I'I'E STRAIGHT UP,

00:07.500 --> 00:09.764
BUT I ADDED A SPRINKLE
OF NUTMEG.

00:09.810 --> 00:11.107
IT'S FESTIVE.

00:11.140 --> 00:13.438
I AM NOTHING
IF NOT FESTIVE.

00:13.480 --> 00:16.404
IT TAKES A BRAVE GIRL
TO AGREE TO A BLIND DATE.
MM-HMM.

00:16.450 --> 00:19.374
EVEN IF YOU ARE
ON THE REBOUND.

00:19.420 --> 00:20.717
WHO TOLD YOU THAT?

00:20.750 --> 00:22.445
YOUR MOTHER.
MY FATHER'S HER BOSS,

00:22.490 --> 00:24.242
AND I GUESS
SHE JUST WANTED TO MAKE SURE

00:24.290 --> 00:25.643
I KNEW WHAT
I WAS GED-I/lâ€”MING INTO.

00:25.690 --> 00:28.079
BUT WHEN SHE SHOWED ME
THAT PICTURE OF YOU --

00:28.120 --> 00:29.758
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

00:29.790 --> 00:31.758
IT WAS A VERY FLA'ITERING
PHOTOGRAPH.

00:31.790 --> 00:33.348
WHAT ACCENT IS THAT?

00:33.400 --> 00:35.288
I'M FROM NOTTINGHAM.
OOH!

00:35.330 --> 00:36.592
[ British accent ]
DID YOU LIVE IN THE WOODS

00:36.630 --> 00:37.494
WITH A BAND OF MERRY MEN?

00:37.530 --> 00:40.499
ARE YOU ASKING ME
IF I'M A HOMOSEXUAL?

00:40.540 --> 00:42.098
[ SIGHS ]

00:42.140 --> 00:44.108
[ Normal voice ] WHAT WERE YOU
DOING IN NOTTINGHAM?

00:44.140 --> 00:45.232
I WAS STUDYING.

00:45.270 --> 00:48.103
DOING MY MASTER'S IN MEDIEVAL
LANGUAGES AND LITERATURE.

00:48.140 --> 00:49.175
THAT'S VERY RANDOM.

00:49.210 --> 00:51.440
HOW LONG WERE YOU
IN ENGLAND FOR?

00:51.480 --> 00:53.311
TWO YEARS.
AND BEFORE THAT?

00:53.350 --> 00:55.215
I GREW UP
ABOUT 20 MINUTES FROM HERE.

00:55.250 --> 00:56.717
BORN AND RAISED
IN FOREST HILL.

00:56.750 --> 00:58.217
CAN WE RECAP?

00:58.250 --> 01:01.788
YOU WERE ONLY IN ENGLAND
FOR T YEARS?

01:01.820 --> 01:03.822
WHAT --
WHAT ARE YOU ASKING ME?

01:03.860 --> 01:06.454
DO THEY HAVE
ANY ALCOHOL HERE?

01:08.530 --> 01:12.239
I HAVE A FULLY STOCKED BAR
IN MY FLAT.

01:12.270 --> 01:14.488
OH?
[ CHUCKLES ]
WE COULD LEAVE RIGHT NOW.

01:14.540 --> 01:15.768
WESTON...

01:15.800 --> 01:17.358
LET ME JUST
BE CLEAR HERE.

01:17.410 --> 01:20.402
THIS DATE'S NOT
GOING VERY WELL FOR YOU.

01:20.440 --> 01:24.149
BUT I'M GONNA STAY
AND ENJOY THIS FESTIVE LA'ITE,

01:24.180 --> 01:26.410
AND THEN
I'M GONNA GO HOME.

01:26.450 --> 01:28.145
ALONE.

01:28.180 --> 01:30.410
BECAUSE THERE'S NOT ENOUGH
ALCOHOL IN THE WORLD

01:30.450 --> 01:31.485
TO GET ME IN BED
WITH YOU.

01:31.520 --> 01:35.115
CAN I KEEP YOUR NUMBER
IN CASE YOU CHANGE YOUR MIND?

01:35.160 --> 01:36.388
I'M GONNA GO NOW.

01:36.430 --> 01:40.594
RIGHT NOW. YEAH.

01:40.630 --> 01:45.567
[ SIREN WAILING,
RADIO CHATTER ]

01:45.600 --> 01:46.828
TWO DATES IN TWO NIGHTS.

01:46.870 --> 01:49.407
SUPERINTENDENT MOM
MUST BE GETTING DESPERATE.

01:49.440 --> 01:51.135
SHE JUST WANTS
TO MAKE SURE

01:51.170 --> 01:53.274
THAT I DON'T END UP
A LONELY SPINSTER.

01:53.310 --> 01:55.505
BESIDES, IT KEEPS ME AWAY
FROM CHEESE PUFFS.

01:55.540 --> 01:56.871
THAT ONE.

01:56.910 --> 01:57.740
UH, ANDY AND I MIGHT BE GOING
TO THE PENNY TONIGHT.

01:57.780 --> 02:00.647
YOU COULD JOIN US
FOR A DRINK INSTEAD.

02:03.590 --> 02:04.409
WHAT IS IT WITH YOU?

02:04.450 --> 02:06.281
YOU'VE BEEN AVOIDING ANDY
FOR WEEKS.

02:06.320 --> 02:07.810
NO, I'M NOT
AVOIDING HER.

02:07.860 --> 02:10.886
I'M JUST SIMPLY MOVING ON
TO A NEW CHAPTER OF MY LIFE.

02:10.930 --> 02:13.490
SOMETHING YOU, MY FRIEND,
SHOULD CONSIDER.

02:13.530 --> 02:15.896
I DON'T KNOW.
[ SIGHS ]

02:15.930 --> 02:18.694
GETTING BACK ON THAT HORSE
SOUNDS A LITTLE EXHAUSTING.

02:18.730 --> 02:21.665
YOU COULD MAKE MY BROTHER
THE HORSE.

02:21.700 --> 02:22.928
GAIL, THAT'S DISGUSTING.

02:22.970 --> 02:24.164
YOU'RE TELLING ME.

02:24.210 --> 02:25.461
[ DOOR OPENS ]

02:25.510 --> 02:27.478
HONEY, I'M HOME!

02:27.510 --> 02:29.239
WHAT?! [ LAUGHS ]

02:29.280 --> 02:31.373
[ LAUGHTER ]

02:31.410 --> 02:33.617
HI!
WE MISSED YOU!
HEY.

02:33.650 --> 02:35.777
IT'S SO -- IT'S SO GOOD
TO SEE YOU GUYS.

02:35.820 --> 02:39.256
THE -- THE -- THE PLACE --
IT LOOKS...THE SAME.

02:39.290 --> 02:41.952
YEAH, IT SMELLS DIFFERENT.
THANK GOD.

02:41.990 --> 02:44.424
TOLD YOU THAT SMELL
WAS YOUR FAULT.

02:44.460 --> 02:47.293
[ CHUCKLES ] HI.

02:47.330 --> 02:49.469
Denise: THANK YOU GUYS SO MUCH
FOR LETTING US STAY HERE.

02:49.500 --> 02:50.922
WE, UM, PROMISE TO KEEP THE MESS
TO A MINIMUM.

02:50.970 --> 02:52.961
YOU'RE STAYING HERE?

02:53.000 --> 02:55.195
I MEAN...

02:55.240 --> 02:57.208
YOU'RE STAYING HERE!

02:57.240 --> 02:58.537
YOU GUYS HAVE
FOUR DAYS OFF.

02:58.570 --> 02:59.935
WHAT ARE YOU
GONNA GET UP TO?

02:59.980 --> 03:01.299
HIT THE TOWN,
PAINT IT RED,

03:01.340 --> 03:02.409
ROCK OUT WITH YOUR --

03:02.450 --> 03:05.305
SHE GETS A LITTLE EXCITED
FIRST THING IN THE MORNING.

03:05.350 --> 03:08.945
IT'S TRUE. I HAD AN ESPRESSO
THIS MORNING, SO [LAUGHS]

03:10.350 --> 03:12.489
JUST GIVE US
LIKE TEN MINUTES,

03:12.520 --> 03:15.387
AND, UH, WE'LL TAKE YOU GUYS
ALL OUT FOR BREAKFAST.

03:15.420 --> 03:16.819
WAIT, A-AREN'T YOU
MISSING SOMETHING?

03:18.460 --> 03:19.495
AAH!

03:19.530 --> 03:20.929
* THE GRAND OLD DUKE
OF YORK *

03:20.960 --> 03:22.928
* HE HAD 10,000 MEN

03:22.970 --> 03:24.926
* HE MARCHED THEM UP
TO THE TOP OF THE HILL *

03:24.970 --> 03:26.562
* AND HE MARCHED THEM
DOWN AGAIN *

03:26.600 --> 03:28.761
* AND WHEN THEY WERE UP,
THEY WERE UP *

03:28.800 --> 03:31.234
* WHEN THEY WERE DOWN,
THEY WERE DOWN *

03:31.270 --> 03:32.476
* AND WHEN THEY WERE ONLY
HALFWAY UP *

03:32.510 --> 03:34.535
Both: * THEY WERE NEITHER UP
NOR DOWN *

03:34.580 --> 03:35.933
WHOA, THE OLD
"DUKE OF YORK" WORKOUT.

03:35.980 --> 03:37.538
HAVEN'T DONE THAT ONE
IN A WHILE.

03:37.580 --> 03:39.673
YEAH, WELL, YOU SHOULD TRY IT.
IT'S KILLER ON THE QUADS.

03:39.720 --> 03:41.517
[ SQUEALS HAPPILY ]
HOW ARE YOU DOING, BUDDY?
YEAH?

03:41.550 --> 03:43.609
CHRIS AND DENISE
JUST GOT IN THIS MORNING,

03:43.650 --> 03:45.641
SO I FIGURED
I'D HELP THEM GET SETTLED.

03:45.690 --> 03:47.453
AND YOU CALLED ME
BECAUSE --

03:47.490 --> 03:49.253
WELL, CLEARLY
I'M RUNNING OUT OF SONGS.

03:49.290 --> 03:50.427
AH, I GATHERED.

03:50.460 --> 03:53.020
AND WE HAVEN'T HUNG OUT
IN A WHILE.

03:53.060 --> 03:55.392
OKAY, SO I KNOW HER...

03:55.430 --> 03:57.569
AND I MET YOU, BUT I HAVEN'T
MET THIS LITTLE GUY.

03:57.600 --> 03:58.760
WHAT'S HIS NAME?

03:58.800 --> 03:59.562
BABY PUPPY.

03:59.600 --> 04:01.659
BABY PUPPY?
THAT'S A GOOD NAME.

04:01.700 --> 04:03.008
VERY LITERAL.
I LIKE IT.

04:03.040 --> 04:05.531
HEY, DO YOU THINK BABY PUPPY'S
EVER BEEN TO THE MOON?
I THINK SO.

04:05.570 --> 04:06.571
DO YOU THINK
HE WANTS TO GO BACK?

04:06.610 --> 04:08.032
'CAUSE I THINK I HEAR
THE ROCKET SHIP STARTING UP.

04:08.080 --> 04:09.672
[ IMITATES
ROCKET SHIP STARTING ]

04:09.710 --> 04:11.803
DOES HE?
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

04:11.850 --> 04:14.444
[ IMITATES ROCKET ENGINE
BLASTING ]

04:14.480 --> 04:15.845
OOH!

04:15.880 --> 04:17.939
WHOA! [ IMITATES
ROCKET ENGINE BLASTING ]

04:17.990 --> 04:22.586
[ CHRISTIAN SQUEALS,
GIGGLES ]

04:22.630 --> 04:25.383
WHOA!

04:25.430 --> 04:28.399
HOT HIBISCUS...

04:28.430 --> 04:29.658
FLAMINGO FIESTA...

04:29.700 --> 04:32.294
OR MANGO MADNESS --

04:32.340 --> 04:34.035
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

04:34.070 --> 04:37.836
I THINK IT LOOKS LIKE
MIAMI THREW UP ON YOUR WALL.

04:37.870 --> 04:39.804
LISTEN -- HAVE YOU EVER BEEN
TO SOUTH BEACH?

04:39.840 --> 04:41.307
I MEAN,
EVERYWHERE YOU LOOK,

04:41.340 --> 04:42.773
THERE ARE BRIGHT,
VIBRANT COLORS.

04:42.810 --> 04:44.641
AND THOSE COLORS
PUT ME IN A GREAT MOOD.

04:44.680 --> 04:48.673
WELL,
THERE ARE OTHER WAYS.

04:48.720 --> 04:54.408
* ...IN NEW YORK CITY
LYING ON THE FLOOR *

04:54.460 --> 04:56.826
OKAY.

04:56.860 --> 04:59.920
I THINK [SIGHS]

04:59.960 --> 05:01.848
I THINK YOU SHOULD GO
WITH THE PINK.

05:01.900 --> 05:03.720
YOU CAN START RIGHT NOW.

05:03.770 --> 05:04.794
MM. I'D LOVE TO,

05:04.830 --> 05:06.695
BUT I'M ON SHIFT
IN AN HOUR.

05:06.740 --> 05:09.436
THAT'S OKAY.
FRANK'S STILL ON HIS HONEYMOON.

05:09.470 --> 05:10.732
SO?

05:10.770 --> 05:12.499
SO, THAT MEANS
OLIVER'S ACTING SERGEANT.

05:12.540 --> 05:13.871
MEANS WE CAN BE
A LITTLE LATE.

05:13.910 --> 05:15.798
* ...BY THE END OF THE NIGHT

05:15.840 --> 05:16.909
OKAY, GREAT.
OKAY.

05:16.950 --> 05:18.406
YEAH. LET'S DO IT.
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

05:18.450 --> 05:19.769
CAN'T WAIT.

05:19.820 --> 05:22.072
I'VE ALWAYS WANTED TO HANG OUT
IN A HOT PINK BEDROOM.

05:22.120 --> 05:23.087
YEAH?
YEAH.

05:23.120 --> 05:24.417
MM.

05:24.450 --> 05:26.884
BECAUSE [SIGHS]

05:26.920 --> 05:28.785
LOOKS GOOD ON YOU.
YEAH.

05:28.820 --> 05:30.481
PINK IS YOUR COLOR.

05:30.530 --> 05:32.088
YOU SURE YOU WANT
TO DO THIS?

05:32.130 --> 05:33.950
NO. [ LAUGHS ] NO.

05:34.000 --> 05:37.697
I DON'T. I DON'T.
NO. I DON'T.

05:37.730 --> 05:38.890
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT YOU,

05:38.930 --> 05:40.795
BUT BABY PUPPY
IS LOOKING HUNGRY.

05:40.840 --> 05:42.603
I'M THINKING...
SCOTTISH FOOD?

05:42.640 --> 05:43.800
HUH?

05:43.840 --> 05:44.829
I KNOW A CUTE LITTLE
DRIVE-TH ROUGH.

05:44.870 --> 05:45.837
IT'S JUST AROUND
THE CORNER.

05:45.870 --> 05:47.838
YOU GRAB HIM.

05:47.880 --> 05:50.098
WHAT?
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:50.150 --> 05:52.710
JUST GREAT.

05:52.750 --> 05:54.547
YOU KNOW?
PARK, CHRISTIAN...

05:54.580 --> 05:56.810
THIS.

05:56.850 --> 05:58.613
UM...

05:58.650 --> 05:59.878
Y-YOU KNOW
WHAT YOU SAID TO ME

05:59.920 --> 06:01.683
ON THE NIGHT
OF THE WEDDING.

06:01.720 --> 06:03.984
I'VE BEEN DOING A LOT
OF THINKING ABOUT IT.

06:04.030 --> 06:05.088
LIKE, I REALLY HAVE.

06:05.130 --> 06:07.997
AND, UH...OKAY, LOOK.

06:08.030 --> 06:09.827
HERE'S THE PROBLEM.

06:09.870 --> 06:12.395
FIRST OF ALL,
THERE'S GAIL.

06:12.440 --> 06:13.964
AND SHE'S MY FRIEND.

06:14.000 --> 06:16.139
OR SOMETHING.

06:16.170 --> 06:18.832
AND YOU GUYS
JUST BROKE UP.

06:18.870 --> 06:21.976
YOU KNOW,
THAT'S REALLY MESSY.

06:22.010 --> 06:23.170
"B," UH, WE WORK TOGETHER,

06:23.210 --> 06:26.509
AND I THINK WE BOTH KNOW THAT
THAT JUST LEADS TO TROUBLE

06:26.550 --> 06:27.574
EVERY SINGLE TIME.

06:27.620 --> 06:28.575
[ CHILD SHRIEKS ]

06:28.620 --> 06:29.985
AND THREE...

06:30.020 --> 06:31.988
I THINK EVERYBODY'S GONNA THINK
IT STARTED UNDERCOVER.

06:32.020 --> 06:34.488
AND IT DIDN'T, BUT I THINK
IT'S GONNA BE REALLY WEIRD TO --

06:34.520 --> 06:36.829
CLYDE!
PLEASE, SOMEBODY!

06:36.860 --> 06:38.020
HANG ON.

06:38.060 --> 06:39.084
[ Crying ] CLYDE.

06:39.130 --> 06:40.199
IT'S OKAY, BUD.

06:40.230 --> 06:43.427
HI, CAN WE PLEASE GET AN
AMBULANCE TO SORAUREN PARK?

06:43.470 --> 06:45.165
MA'AM!
[ SOBBING ]

06:45.200 --> 06:46.997
MA'AM, CAN YOU TELL ME
WHAT HAPPENED?

06:47.040 --> 06:48.064
CLYDE, WAKE UP!
WAKE UP!

06:48.100 --> 06:50.637
MA'AM, I NEED YOU
TO STAND BACK FOR ME, ALL RIGHT?

06:50.670 --> 06:51.705
HE'S PROBABLY
ABOUT 50 YEARS OLD.

06:51.740 --> 06:53.628
I-I DON'T KNOW -- I CAN'T
REALLY SEE HIM FROM HERE.

06:53.680 --> 06:54.738
I NEED YOU TO STAND BACK
FOR ME, OKAY?

06:54.780 --> 06:55.599
[ Sobbing ] OH, NOT MY CLYDE.
I'M A POLICE OFFICER.

06:55.640 --> 06:57.505
YOU KNOW, I REALIZE
THAT'S IMPORTANT.

06:57.550 --> 06:58.972
I JUST -- I-I DON'T KNOW.
I'M NOT NEAR HIM.

06:59.010 --> 07:00.978
I JUST -- I JUST NEED YOU
TO STAND BACK FOR ME.

07:01.020 --> 07:02.487
OKAY.

07:02.520 --> 07:03.612
OKAY, OKAY. JUST, UM...

07:03.650 --> 07:06.483
OKAY, CHRISTIAN? I'M GONNA BE
RIGHT BACK. OKAY, BUD?

07:06.520 --> 07:07.714
JUST HANG TIGHT.

07:07.760 --> 07:09.751
[ LOCK CLICKS ]

07:09.790 --> 07:11.587
[ SOBBING ]

07:11.630 --> 07:12.699
OKAY, MA'AM.

07:12.730 --> 07:13.754
GOT TO GIVE HIM
SOME SPACE, OKAY?

07:13.800 --> 07:15.597
PLEASE.
[ SOBS ]

07:15.630 --> 07:17.188
I NEED YOU TO CALM DOWN.

07:17.230 --> 07:19.835
I NEED YOU TO TALK TO DISPATCH
AND ANSWER THE QUESTIONS, OKAY?

07:19.870 --> 07:21.064
IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.

07:21.100 --> 07:22.704
[ Crying ] OKAY.

07:22.740 --> 07:24.537
HELLO.

07:24.570 --> 07:25.935
I-I'M HIS WIFE.

07:25.970 --> 07:27.005
OKAY, I GOT TO GO BACK.

07:27.040 --> 07:31.602
NO. NO MEDICATION.
HE -- H-HE'S 56.

07:36.590 --> 07:39.957
[ SIRENS WAIL ]

07:47.230 --> 07:49.619
CH RISTIAN?!

07:49.670 --> 07:50.694
[ WAILING CONTINUES ]

07:53.700 --> 07:56.601
[ RADIO CHATTER,
SIREN CHIRPS ]

07:56.640 --> 07:58.904
DID YOU NOTICE
ANYONE NEAR THE TRUCK?

07:58.940 --> 08:00.532
NO.
ANYONE IN THE PARK?

08:00.580 --> 08:02.798
ANYONE PAY SPECIAL ATTENTION
TO CHRISTIAN?

08:02.850 --> 08:04.647
NO. I MEAN, THERE WERE PARENTS
WITH THEIR KIDS,

08:04.680 --> 08:05.840
BUT WE DIDN'T TALK
TO ANYONE.

08:05.880 --> 08:06.972
OKAY. PRICE?

08:07.020 --> 08:08.510
COME HERE.

08:08.550 --> 08:10.518
I WANT YOU TO NOTIFY
THE TRANSIT AUTHORITY,

08:10.550 --> 08:11.619
GET BOLOS OUT -- I NEED A FULL
DESCRIPTION OF CHRISTIAN.

08:11.650 --> 08:12.856
GOT IT.
OKAY. MCNALLY?

08:12.890 --> 08:15.859
[Voice breaking ] YEAH, UM,
HE'S WEARING SOME BLUE JEANS.

08:15.890 --> 08:17.255
HE HAS A GREEN SWEATER,

08:17.290 --> 08:19.155
AND, UH, THE JACKET
THAT HE'S WEARING

08:19.190 --> 08:21.124
IS ORANGE, SILVER, AND WHITE --
IT'S IN STRIPES.

08:21.160 --> 08:22.252
UM...

08:22.300 --> 08:24.723
THE BOOTS THAT HE'S WEARING,
THEY'RE...

08:24.770 --> 08:26.067
NAW.
THEY'RE NAW BLUE.

08:26.100 --> 08:29.137
GO. CRUZ. PECK.

08:29.170 --> 08:30.603
THOSE ARE POSSIBLE WITNESSES
UP THERE.

08:30.640 --> 08:32.062
I WANT YOU TO START
INTERVIEWING THEM, OKAY?

08:32.110 --> 08:33.702
ANYTHING STANDS OUT,
YOU TELL ME RIGHT AWAY.

08:33.740 --> 08:34.900
NO. YOU GUYS, WE'VE ALREADY
KNOCKED ON ALL THE DOORS.

08:34.940 --> 08:36.077
NO, MCNALLY. ..

08:36.110 --> 08:37.771
NO! THEY DON'T KNOW ANYTHING.
THEY DIDN'T SEE ANYTHING.

08:37.810 --> 08:39.107
AN DY! AN DY.

08:39.150 --> 08:40.708
WE NEED TO EXPAND
THE SEARCH.
ANDY, LOOK AT NE.

08:40.750 --> 08:41.739
I KNOW THAT YOU WANT
TO HELP,

08:41.780 --> 08:42.815
BUT RIGHT NOW
YOU TWO ARE WITNESSES,

08:42.850 --> 08:44.784
WHICH MEANS, BEFORE YOU HELP US
WITH THIS SEARCH,

08:44.820 --> 08:45.946
WE NEED TO TAKE
YOUR STATEMENTS.

08:45.990 --> 08:48.049
TRACI'S GONNA TAKE YOU
DOWN TO THE STATION.

08:48.090 --> 08:49.318
COLLINS, MCNALLY.
WITH ME.
HOLD ON.

08:49.360 --> 08:51.123
SAM MY!

08:51.160 --> 08:52.798
MAYBE YOU SHOULD LET TRACI
TAKE THEIR STATEMENTS.

08:52.830 --> 08:54.229
A CHILD WENT MISSING
WHILE IN THE CARE

08:54.260 --> 08:55.659
OF TWO OFFICERS
THAT I TRAINED?

08:55.700 --> 08:56.621
THEY'RE COMING
WITH ME.

08:58.970 --> 09:00.267
GO.

09:01.740 --> 09:04.664
[ SIREN WAILS ]

09:04.710 --> 09:06.871
HOW COULD YOU
LET THIS HAPPEN?

09:06.910 --> 09:09.037
DENISE.
YOU LEFT HIM.

09:09.080 --> 09:10.900
I KNOW. IT WAS JUST
FOR A MINUTE. I THOUGHT
HE WOULD BE OKAY.

09:10.950 --> 09:12.076
[Voice breaking ]
I'M SORRY.

09:12.110 --> 09:13.179
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?
DENISE, PLEASE.

09:13.220 --> 09:15.017
WHAT ARE YOU EVEN
DOING HERE?

09:15.050 --> 09:17.143
AND YOU -- YOU WERE SUPPOSED
TO LOOK AFTER HIM,

09:17.190 --> 09:19.613
NOT LOCK HIM IN THE TRUCK
AND LEAVE HIM BY HIMSELF!

09:19.660 --> 09:20.752
CHRIS.

09:20.790 --> 09:21.916
COLLINS, MCNALLY, LET'S GO.

09:21.960 --> 09:23.587
I'M SORRY.

09:23.630 --> 09:24.881
WE'LL FIND HIM.
I SWEAR.

09:24.930 --> 09:28.320
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

09:28.360 --> 09:30.123
WE'RE GONNA FIND HIM.
ALL RIGHT?

09:30.170 --> 09:31.865
EVERYBODY IS ON IT.
WE'RE GOING TO FIND HIM.

09:31.900 --> 09:33.265
BUT WE NEED TO GO BACK
TO THE STATION,

09:33.300 --> 09:35.131
TALK THROUGH EVERYTHING
THAT HAPPENED TODAY, OKAY?

09:35.170 --> 09:37.866
LET'S GO TO THE STATION.

09:37.910 --> 09:39.935
DOV, THEY'RE GONNA TRY
AND SHUT ME IN SOME ROOM

09:39.980 --> 09:41.732
AND LOCK ME OUT
OF THIS WHOLE THING.

09:41.780 --> 09:43.805
YOU GOT TO BE MY GUY
ON THE GROUND TODAY, OKAY?

09:43.850 --> 09:44.874
OKAY.

09:44.910 --> 09:46.275
OKAY.

09:46.310 --> 09:48.813
OKAY.

09:48.850 --> 09:52.388
MAN:
62-10. 6-2-1-0-5.

09:52.420 --> 09:54.650
[ RADIO CHATTER ]

10:01.800 --> 10:03.620
SOMEBODY
TELL ME SOMETHING.

10:03.670 --> 10:05.729
I GOT SOME HAIR ON THE CAR SEAT,
PROBABLY THE VICTIM'S.

10:05.770 --> 10:07.169
AND SOME TRANSFER
ON THE UPHOLSTERY.

10:07.200 --> 10:09.259
OKAY. BLOOD?
YEAH. ONE SWIPE.

10:09.300 --> 10:11.029
WELL,
IT COULD BE CHRISTIAN'S.

10:11.070 --> 10:12.059
WE CAN'T SAY FOR SURE.

10:12.110 --> 10:14.237
OKAY, PECK, WILL YOU RUN THAT
DOWN TO THE LAB?

10:14.280 --> 10:16.407
HOPEFULLY IT'S OUR ABDUCTOR'S,
AND HE'S IN THE SYSTEM.

10:16.440 --> 10:17.998
ALL RIGHT,
I'LL KEEP YOU POSTED.

10:18.050 --> 10:19.301
ALL RIGHT.

10:22.180 --> 10:24.319
Sam: OKAY, SO,
HER HUSBAND COLLAPSED,

10:24.350 --> 10:25.840
NICK RAN OVER, AND THEN?

10:25.890 --> 10:27.380
NICK WAS DOING CPR
ON THE GUY.

10:27.420 --> 10:29.308
BUT HIS WIFE KEPT GETTING
IN THE WAY,

10:29.360 --> 10:31.749
AND SO I PUT HER
ON THE PHONE WITH DISPATCH,

10:31.790 --> 10:33.690
AND I RAN BACK TO THE TRUCK.
RIGHT BACK TO THE TRUCK.

10:33.730 --> 10:34.856
OKAY, SO, WHY'D YOU GO
TO THE PARK?

10:34.900 --> 10:36.299
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

10:36.330 --> 10:39.265
WHY WERE YOU AND COLLINS
AT THE PARK?

10:39.300 --> 10:42.428
WHY ARE YOU
MAKING THIS PERSONAL?

10:42.470 --> 10:44.358
WHAT?

10:44.410 --> 10:46.799
UH, MCNALLY, I NEED TO KNOW
IF THIS WAS PREMEDITATED

10:46.840 --> 10:48.376
OR A CRIME OF OPPORTUNITY,
OKAY?

10:48.410 --> 10:51.846
SO, DID YOU AND COLLINS
PLAN TO GO TO THE PARK,

10:51.880 --> 10:53.313
OR DID YOU JUST
END UP THERE?

10:53.350 --> 10:55.375
I CALLED CHRIS
THIS MORNING,

10:55.420 --> 10:57.911
AND I SAID
I WOULD TAKE CHRISTIAN.

10:57.950 --> 10:59.884
YOU KNOW, SO HIM AND DENISE
COULD GET SETTLED.

10:59.920 --> 11:01.012
THEN I CALLED NICK,

11:01.060 --> 11:03.153
AND I INVITED HIM
TO THE PARK WITH US.

11:03.190 --> 11:04.179
OKAY, GOOD.
THAT'S EVERYTHING.

11:04.230 --> 11:06.380
UH, YOU CAN SUIT UP
AND, UH, ANSWER THE PHONES.

11:06.430 --> 11:08.022
WHAT? NO. I SHOULD BE OUT THERE
LOOKING FOR CHRISTIAN,

11:08.060 --> 11:09.027
NOT ANSWERING TIP LINES.

11:09.060 --> 11:10.027
COLLINS!
SAM.

11:10.070 --> 11:12.061
NO, IT'S -- IT'S BETTER.

11:15.100 --> 11:19.139
[ P.A. TONE CHIMES,
WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCT LY ]

11:19.170 --> 11:22.276
HEY. THE GUY FROM THE PARK,
HE'S GONNA BE OKAY.

11:22.310 --> 11:23.402
HIS WIFE CALLED
TO SAY THAN KS.

11:23.450 --> 11:25.975
SHE'S GOT YOUR PHONE,
BUT WE'LL -- WE'LL GET IT LATER.

11:26.010 --> 11:27.011
OKAY, THANK YOU.

11:27.050 --> 11:29.143
ANDY.

11:29.180 --> 11:30.408
THIS ISN'T YOUR FAULT.

11:30.450 --> 11:33.487
[ WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER P.A. ]

11:33.520 --> 11:36.887
I HAVE TO GO
GET MY UNIFORM ON.

11:41.260 --> 11:43.467
SHE FEELS BAD ENOUGH
WITHOUT YOU MAKING IT WORSE.

11:47.340 --> 11:49.490
ARE YOU TELLING ME
HOW TO DO MY JOB?

11:49.540 --> 11:51.405
NO, SIR.

11:51.440 --> 11:53.476
OKAY. GOOD.

11:53.510 --> 11:55.398
SO, MIND
YOUR OWN BUSINESS.

11:55.440 --> 11:57.806
SHE'S MY PARTNER.
SHE IS MY BUSINESS.

11:57.850 --> 11:59.442
NOT RIGHT NOW.

11:59.480 --> 12:01.072
TAKE A SEAT.

12:03.950 --> 12:05.815
[ RADIO CHATTER ]

12:05.850 --> 12:07.158
Chloe: DID YOU GUYS
SEE ANYTHING UNUSUAL?

12:07.190 --> 12:09.055
I COME TO THIS PARK
EVERY DAY WITH MY KIDS,

12:09.090 --> 12:11.149
SO I REALLY PAY ATTENTION
TO WHO'S COMING AND GOING.

12:11.190 --> 12:12.999
DID YOU NOTICE ANYTHING
UNUSUAL TODAY?

12:13.030 --> 12:15.021
OKAY, WELL,
I-I DIDN'T SEE HIM TODAY,

12:15.060 --> 12:17.221
BUT THERE'S THIS GUY
WHO HANGS OUT HERE ALL THE TIME,

12:17.270 --> 12:18.498
AND IT'S...WEIRD.

12:18.530 --> 12:19.963
WHY IS IT WEIRD?

12:20.000 --> 12:22.195
HE DOESN'T HAVE ANY KIDS.
OR A DOG.

12:22.240 --> 12:24.037
HE JUST SITS IN HIS VAN
AND WATCHES.

12:24.070 --> 12:26.231
HE WATCHED THE KIDS?
YOU GOT A NAME?

12:26.270 --> 12:28.033
NO, BUT I DO HAVE
THE PLATE NUMBER.

12:28.080 --> 12:29.035
UM...

12:29.080 --> 12:31.901
I TOOK A PICTURE
THE LAST TIME I SAW HIM HERE.

12:31.950 --> 12:33.417
HE DRIVES A WHITE VAN.

12:33.450 --> 12:35.077
THAN KS.

12:35.120 --> 12:36.371
I'M GONNA GO RUN THE PLATE.

12:36.420 --> 12:37.444
THANK YOU.

12:37.490 --> 12:39.048
YEAH.

12:39.090 --> 12:40.250
ANYTHING?

12:40.290 --> 12:42.884
JUST A BUNCH OF PARENTS WORRIED
THAT WE'RE NOT DOING ENOUGH

12:42.930 --> 12:44.181
TO KEEP
THEIR KIDS SAFE, SO...

12:44.230 --> 12:45.322
LET'S KEEP GOING.

12:45.360 --> 12:48.193
[ SIREN WAILS ]

12:48.230 --> 12:49.822
ALL RIGHT,
YOU'RE CLEARED FOR DUTY.

12:49.870 --> 12:51.929
GET ON THE FRONT DESK
AND HANDLE ANY WALK-IN TIPS.

12:55.140 --> 12:56.289
[ CELLPHONE BUZZES ]

12:56.340 --> 12:58.535
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

12:58.570 --> 12:59.901
SWAREK.

12:59.940 --> 13:01.908
HEY, I GOT A PLATE
FOR A SUSPICIOUS VEHICLE

13:01.940 --> 13:03.805
SEEN AROUND THE PARK
ON NUMEROUS OCCASIONS.

13:03.850 --> 13:05.078
GOOD.
WHO OWNS IT?

13:05.110 --> 13:06.475
MM, IT'S REGISTERED
TO A BUSINESS --

13:06.510 --> 13:08.569
4429 AVENUE ROAD.

13:08.620 --> 13:10.247
EXCELLENT.
I'LL MEET YOU THERE.

13:10.290 --> 13:12.588
[ PHONES RINGING ]

13:12.620 --> 13:14.110
WHAT COLOR WAS HIS HAIR?

13:16.290 --> 13:17.985
OKAY, COULD YOU DESCRIBE HIM
ONE MORE TIME?

13:18.030 --> 13:21.124
DENISE IS OKAY.
SHE JUST NEEDED TO LIE DOWN.

13:21.160 --> 13:24.129
THE AMBER ALERT'S
OUT THERE.

13:24.170 --> 13:25.523
LOTS OF TIPS
ARE COMING IN ALREADY,

13:25.570 --> 13:27.060
AND WE'RE DOING
EVERYTHING WE CAN.

13:27.100 --> 13:30.934
DON'T...
GIVE ME THE VICTIM SPEECH.

13:30.970 --> 13:32.938
ACTUALLY TELL ME
WHAT'S GOING ON.

13:35.010 --> 13:37.240
I'M A COP.

13:37.280 --> 13:38.577
TREAT ME LIKE ONE.

13:38.610 --> 13:41.147
WHAT IF IT WAS LEO?

13:41.180 --> 13:43.114
WE'RE FOLLOWING UP
ON A LEAD.

13:43.150 --> 13:44.185
A SUSPECT?

13:44.220 --> 13:46.040
WE DON'T KNOW YET.
WHO IS IT?

13:46.090 --> 13:47.455
IT MIGHT BE NOTHING,
CHRIS.

13:47.490 --> 13:50.050
TRACI, DO NOT KEEP ME
IN THE DARK ON THIS.

13:50.090 --> 13:51.250
MY SON IS OUT THERE.

13:51.290 --> 13:53.497
WHICH IS EXACTLY WHY
YOU'RE IN HERE.

13:53.530 --> 13:56.055
BECAUSE IF LEO
WAS MISSING...

13:56.100 --> 13:57.328
[ SIGHS ]

13:57.370 --> 13:59.964
IF LEO WAS MISSING,
I'D BE OUT THERE,

14:00.000 --> 14:02.298
I'D BE IN A PANIC
TRYING TO HELP,

14:02.340 --> 14:04.501
BUT GETTING IN THE WAY
AND SLOWING EVERYTHING DOWN.

14:04.540 --> 14:06.269
CHRIS, THERE ISN'T ANYTHING
YOU CAN DO

14:06.310 --> 14:07.607
THAT WE AREN'T
ALREADY DOING.

14:07.640 --> 14:10.575
[ SCOFFS LIGHTLY ]

14:15.680 --> 14:18.012
WHAT DID THE MAN LOOK LIKE?

14:18.050 --> 14:20.086
OKAY, HOW OLD IS THE BOY?

14:21.390 --> 14:24.029
WHEN WAS THIS?

14:24.060 --> 14:24.879
YESTERDAY?

14:24.930 --> 14:26.420
MA'AM, THE BOY
THAT WE'RE LOOKING FOR

14:26.460 --> 14:28.325
ACTUALLY DISAPPEARED
THREE HOURS AGO.

14:28.360 --> 14:31.067
NO, I UNDERSTAND THAT,
BUT IT JUST...

14:31.100 --> 14:32.397
WHAT YOU'RE DESCRIBING
SOUNDS LIKE

14:32.430 --> 14:33.931
A FATHER HANGING OUT
WITH HIS SON.

14:33.970 --> 14:35.335
THANK YOU FOR CALLING.

14:35.370 --> 14:36.530
BYE.
[ RECEIVER CLICKS ]

14:36.570 --> 14:38.128
HOW'S IT GOING?

14:38.170 --> 14:39.205
I MEAN, NONE OF THOSE PEOPLE
ARE CALLING IN

14:39.240 --> 14:40.502
WITH ANYTHING THAT'S GONNA
HELP US FIND CHRISTIAN.

14:40.540 --> 14:42.269
THEY'RE JUST TRYING
TO HELP.

14:42.310 --> 14:44.073
I KNOW THEY ARE, BUT...

14:44.110 --> 14:46.146
I JUST WISH
I COULD DO MORE.

14:46.180 --> 14:47.545
I'M SURE DIAZ
FEELS THE SAME.

14:47.580 --> 14:49.616
SO WE GOT TO SHOW HIM
IT'S NOT A LOST CAUSE.

14:49.650 --> 14:52.084
ANY ONE OF THESE TIPS
COULD BRING CHRISTIAN HOME.

14:52.120 --> 14:53.485
I KNOW --
YOU'RE RIGHT.

14:53.520 --> 14:54.953
YOU'RE RIGHT. OKAY.

14:54.990 --> 14:57.584
HELP ME OUT.
[ PHONE RINGS ]

14:57.630 --> 14:59.325
15 DIVISION.

14:59.360 --> 15:00.452
15 DIVISION.

15:00.500 --> 15:01.956
YES.

15:02.000 --> 15:03.319
ALL RIGHT, IS THIS IN REGARD
TO THE MISSING --

15:03.370 --> 15:04.564
YES, THAT'S GREAT.
SO, WHAT TIME WAS THAT?

15:04.600 --> 15:07.034
Sam: SO, MR. FORD?

15:07.070 --> 15:08.935
OH, PLEASE.
CALL ME MR. BISCUIT.

15:08.970 --> 15:10.039
[ CHUCKLES ]
ALL THE KIDS DO.

15:10.070 --> 15:11.332
THAT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

15:11.370 --> 15:14.100
ALL RIGHT,
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

15:14.140 --> 15:15.471
WHERE WERE YOU
TWO HOURS AGO?

15:15.510 --> 15:16.943
I WAS HERE.
[ SCOFFS ]

15:16.980 --> 15:18.572
I SPEND HALF MY LIFE
IN THIS SHOP.

15:18.610 --> 15:19.770
MM-HMM.
[ VELCRO RIPS ]

15:19.810 --> 15:22.074
AND WHO DRIVES THE WHITE VAN
REGISTERED TO YOUR COMPANY?

15:22.120 --> 15:23.212
[ RADIO CHATTER ]

15:23.250 --> 15:24.615
MY LITTLE BROTHER, KEVIN.

15:24.650 --> 15:26.515
HE USES IT
TO MAKE DELIVERIES.

15:26.550 --> 15:29.485
MM-HMM. KEVIN FORD?
DATE OF BIRTH?

15:29.520 --> 15:31.078
DECEMBER 7, 1974.

15:31.130 --> 15:32.620
[ PHONE BEEPS ]

15:32.660 --> 15:34.093
HEY.

15:34.130 --> 15:36.223
I NEED A 1029
ON A KEVIN FORD.

15:36.260 --> 15:37.124
OKAY, CUT THE CRAP,
DETECTIVE.

15:37.170 --> 15:38.364
I-I'M NOT ANSWERING
ANY MORE QUESTIONS

15:38.400 --> 15:39.469
TILL YOU TELL ME
WHAT'S GOING ON.

15:39.500 --> 15:40.569
IS YOUR BROTHER
WORKING TODAY?

15:43.270 --> 15:44.339
I DON'T KNOW.

15:44.370 --> 15:47.077
MAYBE YOU SHOULD,
UH, ASK MY LAWYER.

15:47.110 --> 15:48.236
[ DIALING ]

15:48.280 --> 15:51.977
THANKS FOR YOUR TIME,
MR. FORD.

15:52.010 --> 15:53.272
Marlo: YEAH.

15:53.320 --> 15:55.117
OKAY.
[ PHONE BEEPS ]

15:55.150 --> 15:57.038
[ RADIO CHATTER ]

15:57.090 --> 15:58.182
WHAT IS IT?

15:58.220 --> 16:01.348
TH REE YEARS AGO,

16:01.390 --> 16:03.358
KEVIN FORD WAS QUESTIONED
IN THE DISAPPEARANCE

16:03.390 --> 16:04.618
OF A 4-YEAR-OLD BOY.

16:04.660 --> 16:06.150
HE LIVES
IN THIS NEIGHBORHOOD.

16:06.190 --> 16:09.193
SAM, THEY NEVER FOUND
THE BOY.

16:15.600 --> 16:18.364
Woman on P.A.
DETECTIVE McFADDEN,
PLEASE CALL GUNS AND GANGS

16:18.410 --> 16:19.502
AT EXTENSION 29.

16:19.540 --> 16:22.429
HEY. BABE.

16:22.480 --> 16:24.971
JUST BE CAREFUL.
IT'S -- IT'S HOT.

16:32.720 --> 16:34.756
THIS IS WHY WE MOVED
TO TIMMINS.

16:34.790 --> 16:37.623
OUR LITTLE BOY
IS OUT THERE WITH SOME STRANGER,

16:37.660 --> 16:39.184
SCARED OUT OF HIS MIND.

16:39.230 --> 16:42.597
THIS -- THIS COULD HAVE
HAPPENED ANYWHERE.

16:42.630 --> 16:45.326
BUT IT DIDN'T.

16:45.370 --> 16:46.325
[ SIGHS ]

16:46.370 --> 16:47.667
BABE.

16:52.110 --> 16:53.236
HEY.

16:53.280 --> 16:54.508
HAVE EITHER OF YOU MET

16:54.540 --> 16:56.633
OR HEARD OF A GUY
NAMED KEVIN FORD?

16:56.680 --> 16:59.205
I'VE NEVER HEARD
THAT NAME BEFORE.

16:59.250 --> 17:02.469
WHO IS HE?
DOES HE HAVE CHRISTIAN?

17:02.520 --> 17:05.114
ALL I CAN TELL YOU IS
WE'RE WAITING FOR A WARRANT.

17:07.220 --> 17:09.279
YOU'RE GONNA PICK UP FORD
AT THE WAREHOUSE.

17:09.320 --> 17:11.720
I'LL SEND EPSTEIN WITH PRICE
AND A COUPLE OF UNIFORMS

17:11.760 --> 17:12.829
TO SEARCH HIS HOUSE,

17:12.860 --> 17:15.328
UNLESS YOU WANT TO SECOND-GUESS
ME ON THAT ONE, TOO.

17:17.130 --> 17:19.360
[ RADIO CHATTER ]

17:23.510 --> 17:24.499
DOV.

17:24.540 --> 17:26.804
EPSTEIN,
WE GOT TO MOVE.

17:26.840 --> 17:27.909
IS THAT A WARRANT?

17:30.280 --> 17:32.145
I CAN'T.
I'M DYING IN HERE!

17:32.180 --> 17:34.512
IF THE GUY WE'RE GOING AFTER
TOOK CHRISTIAN,

17:34.550 --> 17:36.370
I'LL LET YOU KILL HIM
WITH YOUR BARE HANDS --

17:36.420 --> 17:39.082
AFTER WE GET HIM BACK.

17:45.330 --> 17:46.422
[ SIGHS ]

17:46.460 --> 17:48.223
THANKS SO MUCH
FOR DOING THIS.

17:48.260 --> 17:51.297
KID GOES MISSING, IT'S PRETTY
MUCH TOP OF THE PILE.

17:51.330 --> 17:54.367
SO, HOW LONG UNTIL WE KNOW
IF THE DNA'S IN THE SYSTEM?

17:54.400 --> 17:56.129
COUPLE HOURS, MAYBE MORE.

17:56.170 --> 17:59.105
AND YOU -- YOU CAN'T RUSH IT?
MAKE IT GO FASTER?

17:59.140 --> 18:01.802
SURE, I'LL JUST RUSH
THE POLYMERASE CHAIN REACTION.

18:01.840 --> 18:03.307
NOT LIKE IT'S IMPORTANT.

18:03.350 --> 18:04.601
MAYBE YOU COULD CHIP IN.

18:04.650 --> 18:07.346
HOW ARE YOU AT IDENTIFYING
SHORT TANDEM REPEATS?

18:07.380 --> 18:09.109
YOU COULD HAVE JUST SAID "NO."

18:09.150 --> 18:11.345
I DID FIND SOMETHING
INTERESTING.

18:11.390 --> 18:13.654
THE TYPING CAME BACK
INCONSISTENT.

18:13.690 --> 18:15.180
IN ENGLISH.

18:15.220 --> 18:16.585
THE BLOOD SAMPLE
YOU BROUGHT IN,

18:16.620 --> 18:18.520
IT CONTAINED
TWO DIFFERENT TYPES OF BLOOD.

18:18.560 --> 18:20.391
ONE WAS "A" TYPE,
THE OTHER "0" NEGATIVE.

18:20.430 --> 18:21.897
THERE WERE TWO ABDUCTORS?

18:21.930 --> 18:23.466
OR ONE OF THE SAMPLE'S
THE KID'S.

18:23.500 --> 18:25.491
I'M CHECKING IT AGAINST
CHRISTIAN'S HAIR AND SALIVA

18:25.530 --> 18:26.497
FROM HIS STUFFED ANIMAL.

18:26.530 --> 18:29.397
I GOT TO MAKE A CALL.

18:29.440 --> 18:31.135
OLIVER, IT'S PECK.

18:31.170 --> 18:34.139
[ SIRENS WAILING ]

18:37.910 --> 18:40.413
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

18:42.750 --> 18:44.240
[ RADIO CHATTER ]

18:44.290 --> 18:45.882
OLIVER SAID THERE MIGHT
BE TWO OF THEM,

18:45.920 --> 18:47.285
SO STAY SHARP.

18:47.320 --> 18:50.289
IS, UH, KEVIN FORD HERE?
Kevin: OH, OFFICERS.

18:50.330 --> 18:51.888
YEAH, MY BROTHER TOLD ME
YOU WERE LOOKING FOR ME.

18:51.930 --> 18:53.397
IS THERE SOMETHING
I CAN DO TO HELP?

18:53.430 --> 18:54.795
AH! OHH!

18:54.830 --> 18:56.149
WHAT THE HELL?!

18:56.200 --> 18:57.929
Sam: WHERE'S CHRISTIAN?
WHO? [ GROANS ]

18:57.970 --> 18:59.528
NOTHING IN THE VAN.

18:59.570 --> 19:01.265
JUST TELL ME
WHAT'S GOING ON.

19:01.300 --> 19:03.200
OUR PLATOON IS TEARING YOUR
HOUSE APART RIGHT NOW, KEVIN.

19:03.240 --> 19:04.059
WHERE IS HE?

19:04.110 --> 19:05.407
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

19:05.440 --> 19:07.579
AAH!

19:07.610 --> 19:09.578
[ RADIO CHATTER ]

19:12.810 --> 19:14.277
DID THEY FIND CHRISTIAN?

19:14.320 --> 19:15.275
[ RECEIVER CLICKS ]

19:15.320 --> 19:17.447
WE SEARCHED HIS HOUSE,
HIS VAN.

19:17.490 --> 19:19.242
WE SEARCHED THE WAREHOUSE.

19:19.290 --> 19:20.359
NOTHING.

19:22.990 --> 19:24.389
HEY. IT'S OKAY.

19:24.430 --> 19:25.556
IT'S OKAY.
IT'S OKAY.

19:25.590 --> 19:27.490
WE'RE GETTING CLOSER.

19:27.530 --> 19:30.226
WE'RE GETTING CLOSER,
OKAY?

19:30.270 --> 19:32.261
OKAY, I DON'T -- I DON'T WANT
TO BE DIFFICULT,

19:32.300 --> 19:33.267
BUT WHERE'S MY LAWYER?

19:33.300 --> 19:34.699
OH, THEY'RE ON THEIR WAY.

19:34.740 --> 19:36.890
THEY'LL BE HERE SOON.

19:36.940 --> 19:39.306
WHO'S THIS?

19:39.340 --> 19:40.932
THAT IS
CHRISTIAN MURPHY.

19:40.980 --> 19:41.878
THIS IS CHRISTIAN.

19:41.910 --> 19:43.969
THIS IS THE -- THE BOY
YOU'RE LOOKING FOR.

19:44.010 --> 19:46.240
YEAH, HE WAS
AT SORAUREN PARK TODAY.

19:46.280 --> 19:47.178
DO YOU KNOW THAT PARK?

19:47.220 --> 19:49.415
YEAH, I-I DRIVE BY IT
ON THE WAY TO WORK.

19:49.450 --> 19:51.338
I-I'VE NEVER SEEN
THIS KID BEFORE.

19:51.390 --> 19:52.448
YOU'RE SURE?

19:52.490 --> 19:54.685
YEAH, YEAH, I'M SURE.
I'M PRETTY GOOD WITH FACES.

19:54.720 --> 19:57.655
OKAY. YOU SPEND A LOT OF TIME
AROUND CHILDREN, RIGHT?

19:57.690 --> 19:59.783
WATCHING THEM,
HANGING OUT WITH THEM.

19:59.830 --> 20:03.220
MY BROTHER AND I
RUN A BUSINESS --

20:03.270 --> 20:05.522
A BUSINESS WE INHERITED.

20:05.570 --> 20:08.437
WE MAKE ENOUGH
TO GET BY...

20:08.470 --> 20:10.734
KIDS LEAVE
WITH SMILES ON THEIR FACES.

20:10.770 --> 20:13.432
WIN/WIN --
THERE'S NOTHING WRONG WITH THAT.

20:13.480 --> 20:15.368
EXCEPT IF YOU'RE
MARCUS HARTLEY, RIGHT?

20:15.410 --> 20:17.275
HE CAME TO YOUR STORE
TH REE YEARS AGO,

20:17.310 --> 20:18.379
AND THEN HE DISAPPEARED.

20:18.410 --> 20:19.809
THAT'S NOT EXACTLY
A WIN/WIN.

20:19.850 --> 20:22.546
NO.
THAT'S A TRAGEDY.

20:22.580 --> 20:25.310
SO, WHAT?
YOU THINK...

20:25.350 --> 20:27.284
THE SAME PERSON
TOOK CHRISTIAN?

20:27.320 --> 20:29.413
WELL, WHY DON'T YOU TELL US,
KEVIN?

20:29.460 --> 20:31.348
IS THAT WHAT YOU DO?

20:31.390 --> 20:33.324
IS THAT YOUR "THING"?

20:33.360 --> 20:34.657
YOU MEET THESE KIDS
AT THE STORE,

20:34.700 --> 20:35.519
YOU GET TO KNOW THEM,

20:35.560 --> 20:37.391
THEN YOU START HANGING OUT
AT THE PARK,

20:37.430 --> 20:39.261
AND ALL OF A SUDDEN,
YOU'RE A FAMILIAR FACE.

20:39.300 --> 20:41.291
I MEAN, IT'S PRETTY EASY
TO TAKE IT ONE STEP FURTHER.

20:41.340 --> 20:42.568
SHUT UP.
SHUT UP!

20:42.600 --> 20:43.908
MAYBE YOU EVEN
BRING A PARTNER ALONG!

20:43.940 --> 20:45.430
HUH?
YOU MAKE ME SICK!

20:45.470 --> 20:47.700
DO I?!
I'M GONNA ASK YOU ONE MORE TIME!

20:47.740 --> 20:51.301
WHERE'S CHRISTIAN?

20:51.350 --> 20:53.716
I WOULD REALLY LIKE
TO HELP YOU, OFFICER...
[ SCOFFS ]

20:53.750 --> 20:55.547
...BUT NOW IT'S MY TURN.

20:55.580 --> 20:58.048
WHERE THE HELL'S MY LAWYER?

20:58.090 --> 20:59.011
Sam:
UH, SHE'S ON HER WAY.

20:59.050 --> 21:00.688
SHE'LL BE HERE
IN A FEW MINUTES.

21:00.720 --> 21:01.687
HEY.
HEY. WHAT'S UP?

21:01.720 --> 21:02.914
WE GOT A CALL
ON THE TIP LINE.

21:02.960 --> 21:04.587
GUY JUST HAULED A SCREAMING
TODDLER OUT OF A MOVIE THEATER

21:04.630 --> 21:05.483
AT DUNDAS SQUARE.

21:05.530 --> 21:07.020
THE BOY MATCHED
CHRISTIAN'S DESCRIPTION,

21:07.060 --> 21:08.925
BUT THEY DISAPPEARED
BEFORE SECURITY COULD GRAB THEM.

21:08.960 --> 21:10.928
ALL RIGHT, WHEN WAS THAT?
TEN MINUTES AGO?

21:10.970 --> 21:11.766
OKAY, DID SECURITY
GET A VISUAL?

21:11.800 --> 21:13.461
YEAH, THEY'RE E-MAILING ME
RIGHT NOW.

21:13.500 --> 21:14.637
OKAY, YOU GOT TO FORWARD THAT
TO NASH.

21:14.670 --> 21:15.762
LET'S GO.

21:15.800 --> 21:16.892
NASH, OPEN YOUR E-MAIL.

21:16.940 --> 21:18.567
MCNALLY'S SENDING YOU
A FILE.

21:18.610 --> 21:19.861
I'LL HAVE IT UP
IN A SECOND.

21:19.910 --> 21:21.377
OKAY.

21:21.410 --> 21:22.377
WHAT'S GOING ON?

21:22.410 --> 21:23.502
WE HAVE
A SURVEILLANCE PHOTO

21:23.550 --> 21:25.040
OF SOMEONE WHO MIGHT BE
OUR SUSPECT.

21:25.080 --> 21:26.741
IT'S DOWNLOADING.

21:33.390 --> 21:34.618
THAT'S CHRISTIAN.

21:34.660 --> 21:37.481
DO YOU KNOW
WHO THIS GUY IS?

21:37.530 --> 21:39.384
OH, MY GOD.

21:39.430 --> 21:41.751
THAT'S --
THAT'S GENE MaCKENZIE.

21:41.800 --> 21:43.665
HE WAS CHRISTIAN'S SOCCER COACH
IN TIMMONS.

21:50.970 --> 21:53.336
Woman on P.A. DETECTIVE WILKINS,
PLEASE PICK UP LINE 1.

21:53.380 --> 21:54.938
WHAT IS GENE DOING HERE?

21:54.980 --> 21:57.972
RIGHT NOW WE NEED TO FOCUS
ON FINDING HIM, OKAY?

21:58.010 --> 22:00.672
SO, WHAT ELSE CAN YOU TWO
TELL ME ABOUT HIM?

22:00.720 --> 22:02.813
HE'S 32. 33, MAYBE.

22:02.850 --> 22:03.782
HE --
HE LIVES IN TIMMONS.

22:03.820 --> 22:06.539
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]
I DON'T KNOW WHAT ELSE.

22:06.590 --> 22:07.955
SHOULD HAVE BEEN ABLE
TO SEE IT.

22:07.990 --> 22:09.810
YOU KNOW, HE USED TO DOTE
ON CHRISTIAN --

22:09.860 --> 22:11.680
GIVE HIM ALL SORTS
OF SPECIAL ATTENTION?

22:11.730 --> 22:12.856
CHRIS, DON'T DO THIS
TO YOURSELF.

22:12.890 --> 22:14.096
THERE'S NO WAY
YOU COULD HAVE KNOWN.

22:14.130 --> 22:15.620
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.
HE'S A PREDATOR,

22:15.660 --> 22:16.558
AND I'M A POLICE OFFICER.

22:16.600 --> 22:18.090
I SHOULD'VE BEEN ABLE
TO TELL.
STOP IT.

22:18.130 --> 22:20.928
MY SON'S MISSING, AND I CAN'T
EVEN LOOK FOR HIM!

22:23.470 --> 22:25.938
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

22:31.550 --> 22:33.871
[ GLASS CLINKS ]
[ SIGHS ]

22:39.590 --> 22:40.887
WE GOT TO CLEAN THIS UP.

22:40.920 --> 22:43.889
THERE'S A FIRST AID KIT
IN THE LOUNGE.

22:43.930 --> 22:47.127
YOU GOT TO FIND HIM,
TRACE.

22:47.160 --> 22:48.627
I'M SORRY.
COME ON.
IT'S OKAY.

22:48.660 --> 22:52.721
PDU IS ON LINE 1
FOR DETECTIVE WILKINS.
DETECTIVE WILKINS...

22:52.770 --> 22:55.091
THIS LITTLE WITCH HUNT
OF YOURS IS OVER.

22:55.140 --> 22:57.961
I KNOW YOU HAVE SURVEILLANCE
PHOTOS OF THE ABDUCT OR.

22:58.010 --> 22:59.466
AND HOW
DO YOU KNOW THAT?

22:59.510 --> 23:00.602
I GET PAID TO KNOW.

23:00.640 --> 23:02.528
CHECK THE PHOTOS.
I'M NOT ON THEM.

23:02.580 --> 23:04.798
DOES THE NAME GENE MaCKENZIE
MEAN ANYTHING TO YOU?

23:04.850 --> 23:06.101
NO, DETECTIVE,
IT DOESN'T.

23:06.150 --> 23:08.118
DOES IT MEAN ANYTHING
TO YOU?
MR. FORD.

23:08.150 --> 23:10.789
WHY DOES A GUY WITH NO KIDS HAVE
A SWING SET IN HIS BACKYARD?

23:10.820 --> 23:12.845
WOW. THAT'S YOUR CASE
AGAINST ME?

23:12.890 --> 23:15.051
IT WAS THERE
WHEN I BOUGHT THE HOUSE.

23:15.090 --> 23:16.910
MR. FORD, PLEASE.
LET ME HANDLE THIS.

23:16.960 --> 23:18.780
DETECTIVE,

23:18.830 --> 23:20.559
YOU REALLY WANT TO
DRAG THIS OUT?

23:20.600 --> 23:21.589
I HAVE PLACES TO BE.

23:21.630 --> 23:23.689
WE HAVEN'T LOCATED
THE KID YET,

23:23.730 --> 23:25.493
SO NO ONE'S GOING ANYWHERE.
[ DOOR BUZZES ]

23:25.530 --> 23:27.964
OLIVER WANTS TO SEE EVERYONE
IN PARADE RIGHT AWAY.

23:28.000 --> 23:29.934
EPSTEIN, WE'RE IN THE MIDDLE
OF AN INTERVIEW.

23:29.970 --> 23:32.006
IT'S NOT A REQUEST.

23:32.040 --> 23:33.871
[ RADIO CHATTER ]

23:37.550 --> 23:39.609
[ SIGHS ]

23:41.020 --> 23:42.942
WE HAVE A VISUAL I.D.
OF OUR ABDUCTOR.

23:42.980 --> 23:44.140
THIS IS GENE MaCKENZIE.

23:44.190 --> 23:46.909
HE'S IN OUR SYSTEM FOR AN
AGGRAVATED ASSAULT BACK IN '95.

23:46.950 --> 23:49.510
HE'S CHRISTIAN'S SOCCER COACH
BACK IN TIMMONS.

23:49.560 --> 23:52.950
ALSO, A SWIMMING INSTRUCTOR
AND A LITTLE-LEAGUE COACH THERE.

23:52.990 --> 23:54.890
WHY WOULDN'T HE GRAB CHRISTIAN
IN TIMMONS?

23:54.930 --> 23:56.454
I MEAN,
WHY FOLLOW HIM HERE?

23:56.500 --> 23:57.967
MAYBE TO DISTANCE HIMSELF
AS A SUSPECT.

23:58.000 --> 23:58.989
WE DON'T KNOW.

23:59.030 --> 24:00.463
WELL,
IS HE WORKING ALONE?

24:00.500 --> 24:01.467
WE DON'T KNOW.

24:01.500 --> 24:02.489
WHAT WE DO KNOW

24:02.540 --> 24:04.701
IS THAT CHRISTIAN
SEEMS TO BE ALIVE AND WELL.

24:04.740 --> 24:06.469
WHERE WAS THE LAST
VISUAL CONFIRMATION?

24:06.510 --> 24:07.977
IT WAS AT THE MOVIE THEATER
AT DUNDAS SQUARE.

24:08.010 --> 24:08.908
30 MINUTES AGO.

24:08.940 --> 24:11.204
OKAY, WE'RE GONNA CANVASS
THE ENTIRE AREA.

24:11.250 --> 24:13.548
GUYS, WE'RE LOOKING
FOR A GREEN HATCHBACK.

24:13.580 --> 24:16.071
THE LICENSE PLATE IS
ALPHA-YAN KEE-X-RAY-LIMA 112.

24:16.120 --> 24:17.246
LET'S GO FIND THIS BOY.

24:17.280 --> 24:20.613
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

24:20.660 --> 24:21.888
CRUZ.

24:23.060 --> 24:24.948
YOU GOT TO
CUT FORD LOOSE.

24:24.990 --> 24:27.026
WHAT -- OLIVER.

24:27.060 --> 24:28.596
WHAT?

24:28.630 --> 24:30.723
LOOK, MaCKENZIE MIGHT NOT
BE WORKING ALONE.

24:30.770 --> 24:33.739
FORD'S VAN WAS SEEN NEAR THE
PLAYGROUND NUMEROUS TIMES, OKAY?

24:33.770 --> 24:36.568
PLUS, HE'S GOT TIES TO AN
UNSOLVED CHILD-ABDUCTION CASE.

24:36.600 --> 24:38.568
I MEAN, WE LET HIM GO,
WE'RE MAKING A MISTAKE.

24:38.610 --> 24:40.498
YOUR CALL.

24:43.240 --> 24:44.969
CUT HIM LOOSE.

24:45.010 --> 24:45.999
WHAT?

24:49.580 --> 24:50.945
YES, SIR.

24:54.790 --> 24:58.681
ALL RIGHT. [ SIGHS ]

24:58.730 --> 25:01.096
WHAT THE...

25:01.130 --> 25:03.724
"WHAT THE" WHAT?

25:03.770 --> 25:05.192
HOLLY, "WHAT THE" WHAT?

25:05.230 --> 25:06.094
WHAT?

25:06.130 --> 25:07.995
I DON'T WANT TO PLAY
"WHO'S ON FIRST?"

25:08.040 --> 25:09.564
JUST TELL ME
WHAT'S GOING ON.

25:09.600 --> 25:12.603
WHAT DOES THIS MEAN?

25:14.340 --> 25:16.103
BACKGROUND CHECK
ON MacKENZIE

25:16.140 --> 25:18.176
IDENTIFIED TWO
OUT-OF-TOWN ADDRESSES.

25:18.210 --> 25:20.610
HE HAS AN AUNT IN ESSEX
AND A GRANDFATHER IN KINGSVILLE.

25:20.650 --> 25:22.743
WE'VE NOTIFIED LOCAL POLICE
IN BOTH JURISDICTIONS.

25:22.780 --> 25:25.010
AND I GOT A CELLPHONE NUMBER,
BUT HE'S NOT ANSWERING.

25:25.050 --> 25:28.110
GUYS, I HAVE SOMETHING.

25:28.160 --> 25:30.628
WE PULLED TWO DNA SAMPLES
FROM THE CRIME SCENE.

25:30.660 --> 25:32.252
ONE OF THEM
WAS GENE MacKENZIE'S,

25:32.290 --> 25:33.848
AND THE OTHER ONE
WASN'T IN THE SYSTEM,

25:33.900 --> 25:35.720
BUT IT MATCHES THE HAIR
WE FOUND ON THE CAR SEAT.

25:35.760 --> 25:36.988
SO IT'S CHRISTIAN'S?

25:37.030 --> 25:39.169
[ SIGHS ]

25:39.200 --> 25:42.567
THE TWO SAMPLES
ARE A GENETIC MATCH.

25:42.600 --> 25:44.807
GENE MacKENZIE
IS CHRISTIAN'S FATHER.

25:47.640 --> 25:50.006
[ FOLDER CLOSES ]

25:52.280 --> 25:53.645
HEY.

25:53.680 --> 25:55.568
WHERE'S CHRIS?

25:55.620 --> 25:56.917
I DON'T KNOW.
HE'S GETTING ME SOME WATER.
[ FOLDER SLAMS ]

25:56.950 --> 25:58.212
WHAT IS THIS?

25:58.250 --> 26:00.889
DNA ANALYSIS FOR GENE...

26:00.920 --> 26:02.683
AND FOR CHRISTIAN.

26:02.720 --> 26:05.052
OH, GOD.

26:05.090 --> 26:06.853
THAT'S WHY GENE TOOK HIM,
ISN'T IT?

26:06.890 --> 26:09.120
I DIDN'T KNOW.

26:09.160 --> 26:10.252
YOU HAVE TO TELL CHRIS.

26:10.300 --> 26:11.198
PLEASE, DOV --
PLEASE --

26:11.230 --> 26:13.733
YOU HAVE TO TELL CHRIS
HE'S NOT THE FATHER!

26:13.770 --> 26:16.295
DENISE?

26:43.160 --> 26:44.764
NO HITS ON THE TRAVEL BOLO.

26:44.800 --> 26:47.189
GENE'S PROBABLY LAYING LOW
WITH CHRISTIAN.

26:47.230 --> 26:48.367
FOR NOW.

26:48.400 --> 26:50.197
YEAH,
THE QUESTION IS WHERE?

26:52.410 --> 26:54.332
I NEED TO TALK TO HER.

26:54.380 --> 26:57.338
ARE YOU SURE
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA?

26:57.380 --> 26:59.769
NO.

26:59.810 --> 27:01.175
OKAY.

27:06.450 --> 27:08.008
CHRIS -- CHRIS,
I DIDN'T KNOW

27:08.060 --> 27:09.948
UNTIL DOV SHOWED ME
THAT PIECE OF PAPER.

27:09.990 --> 27:11.252
YOU HAVE TO BELIEVE ME.
LOOK --

27:11.290 --> 27:13.155
DENISE.
IF YOU KNEW WHAT GENE WAS LIKE
WHEN WE WERE TOGETHER.

27:13.190 --> 27:14.896
DENISE.
BUT I NEVER THOUGHT
HE'D DO SOMETHING LIKE --

27:14.930 --> 27:15.897
DENISE!

27:15.930 --> 27:17.898
[ PHONE RINGING ]

27:17.930 --> 27:19.795
LOOK, IT'S --
IT'S OKAY.

27:19.830 --> 27:21.138
OKAY?

27:21.170 --> 27:23.161
WHATEVER
THE DNA TEST SAYS...

27:23.200 --> 27:25.407
CHRISTIAN IS OUR SON.

27:25.440 --> 27:26.509
[ GASPS SOFTLY ]

27:26.540 --> 27:29.008
THE ONLY THING THAT MATTERS NOW
IS BRINGING HIM HOME.

27:29.040 --> 27:30.871
OKAY.

27:30.910 --> 27:33.071
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]
SO, WHAT DO WE DO?

27:33.110 --> 27:35.749
WHERE'S YOUR PHONE?

27:37.450 --> 27:39.179
WE'RE GONNA CALL GENE.

27:41.020 --> 27:42.783
YOU'RE GONNA TELL HIM
YOU'RE SORRY.

27:42.820 --> 27:44.321
YOU'RE GONNA TELL HIM
YOU KNOW WHAT HE DID.

27:44.360 --> 27:46.089
BUT YOU HAVEN'T TOLD ANYONE
HE HAS CHRISTIAN.

27:46.130 --> 27:47.256
WHAT?

27:47.290 --> 27:49.292
YOU'RE GONNA TELL HIM YOU TWO
CAN WORK THIS OUT TOGETHER.

27:49.330 --> 27:51.161
WHAT IF HE DOESN'T
BELIEVE ME?

27:51.200 --> 27:53.020
HE WILL.

27:53.070 --> 27:54.833
BECAUSE HE WANTS TO.

27:54.870 --> 27:58.237
[ Beeps, ringing ]

28:02.940 --> 28:04.942
GENE: Is this what it takes
to get your attention?

28:04.980 --> 28:06.800
[ SIGHS ]
I KNOW YOU HAVE CHRISTIAN,

28:06.850 --> 28:07.976
BUT WE CAN CLEAR THIS UP.

28:08.020 --> 28:09.169
NO ONE ELSE NEEDS TO KNOW.

28:09.220 --> 28:10.881
He's my son.

28:10.920 --> 28:12.888
You can't keep him from me.

28:12.920 --> 28:14.979
You can't let another man
pretend to be hIS father!

28:15.020 --> 28:16.089
I'm his father!

28:16.120 --> 28:17.212
[ Christian cries ]

28:17.260 --> 28:18.818
GENE:
It's okay, buddy. It's okay.

28:18.860 --> 28:20.088
Don't -- Don't cry.
Come on.

28:20.130 --> 28:21.757
LET ME TALK TO CHRISTIAN.

28:21.800 --> 28:23.893
CHRISTIAN: [Whimpers]
I want to go home!

28:23.930 --> 28:25.124
GENE!

28:25.170 --> 28:27.968
GENE: He's fine.

28:31.070 --> 28:32.901
THEN I'LL COME MEET YOU.

28:32.940 --> 28:34.931
No.

28:34.980 --> 28:37.301
I WON'T TELL CHRIS.

28:37.340 --> 28:40.912
I WON'T TELL ANYONE.

28:40.950 --> 28:42.838
[Voice breaking ]
WE CAN CLEAR THIS UP,
GENE, JUST THE TWO OF US.

28:42.880 --> 28:45.110
PLEASE,
JUST TELL ME WHERE YOU ARE.

28:45.150 --> 28:47.015
[ Christian cries ]

28:49.220 --> 28:51.427
HE'S UPSET, GENE.

28:51.460 --> 28:52.825
HE NEEDS HIS MOM.

28:52.860 --> 28:54.748
I'M BEGGING YOU.
PLEASE?

28:54.800 --> 28:55.892
[ SNIFFLES ]

28:55.930 --> 28:57.921
IF YOU LOVE CHRISTIAN...

28:59.900 --> 29:00.992
[ RAPS TABLE ]

29:01.040 --> 29:02.098
IF YOU LOVE YOUR SON,

29:02.140 --> 29:03.539
YOU'LL LET ME SEE HIM.

29:03.570 --> 29:06.505
Say it again.

29:06.540 --> 29:08.030
Say he's my son.

29:08.080 --> 29:10.378
HE'S YOUR SON, GENE.

29:10.410 --> 29:13.846
We're -- We're, uh,
we're at the Play Palace.

29:13.880 --> 29:14.949
I've been trying
to calm him down.

29:14.980 --> 29:16.049
Come on, buddy.

29:16.080 --> 29:17.843
I got -- I got to go.

29:17.890 --> 29:19.346
[ Dial tone ]

29:19.390 --> 29:21.017
[ CRIES ]

29:21.060 --> 29:22.015
THAT WAS GOOD.

29:22.060 --> 29:23.925
YOU DID GOOD.

29:23.960 --> 29:26.326
[ SOBBING ]

29:26.360 --> 29:28.499
SECURITY'S BEEN NOTIFIED,

29:28.530 --> 29:30.350
AND THEY'LL CALL US WHEN THEY
GET A VISUAL CONFIRMATION!

29:30.400 --> 29:31.492
[ SIREN WAILS ]

29:31.530 --> 29:34.169
DOV.

29:34.200 --> 29:35.269
[ RADIO CHATTER ]

29:35.300 --> 29:36.460
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

29:36.500 --> 29:38.809
PRICE, YOU'RE WITH ME.

29:40.110 --> 29:41.532
LET'S GO.

29:41.580 --> 29:46.074
[ SIRENS WAILING,
ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

29:46.110 --> 29:49.216
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

29:49.250 --> 29:51.309
FAN OUT.
EVERYBODY COVER AN EXIT.

29:51.350 --> 29:54.410
IF THIS GUY RUNS, I WANT HIM
TO RUN INTO ONE OF YOU.

29:54.460 --> 29:55.586
EPSTEIN, YOU'RE WITH ME.
DIAZ?

29:55.620 --> 29:57.850
I KNOW.
I'LL STAY HERE.

30:01.930 --> 30:04.194
[ GAMES CLANGING ]

30:08.340 --> 30:09.830
YEAH, A LITTLE HIGHER.

30:09.870 --> 30:11.599
GOOD! OH! OH!

30:11.640 --> 30:12.902
ALMOST!

30:12.940 --> 30:14.009
[ Chuckling ] ALMOST!

30:14.040 --> 30:15.177
[ SHOUTS ]

30:15.210 --> 30:18.077
GOT IT! YEAH!

30:18.110 --> 30:19.509
OKAY, ONE MORE.
ONE MORE.

30:19.550 --> 30:21.177
GOOD BOY!

30:21.220 --> 30:23.370
I'VE GOT HIM
IN THE NORTHEAST CORNER.

30:23.420 --> 30:26.139
LOOK HOW MANY TICKETS
WE'RE GETTING, BUDDY. NICE!

30:26.190 --> 30:28.454
LOOK AT THIS.
LOOK AT HOW MANY TICKETS WE GOT.

30:28.490 --> 30:29.411
GENE MacKENZIE.

30:39.530 --> 30:41.134
THERE'S NOWHERE TO GO.

30:41.170 --> 30:42.194
WHERE'S DENISE?

30:42.240 --> 30:43.901
SHE'S NOT COMING.

30:43.940 --> 30:44.929
COME ON, GENE.

30:46.410 --> 30:47.365
THIS IS MY SON.

30:47.410 --> 30:49.970
I KNOW. SO LET'S NOT DO THIS
IN FRONT OF HIM.

30:50.010 --> 30:52.149
IF YOU EVER COME NEAR
MY FAMILY AGAIN --

30:52.180 --> 30:54.045
HE'S NOT YOUR FAMILY!
LET GO OF MY SON.

30:54.080 --> 30:56.378
HE'S NOT YOUR FAMILY!

30:58.920 --> 31:01.081
HEY, BUDDY.

31:02.960 --> 31:04.427
OKAY.

31:04.460 --> 31:06.189
BUDDY.
MR. MacKENZIE, I NEED YOU
TURN AROUND, ALL RIGHT?

31:06.230 --> 31:07.185
PUT YOUR HANDS
ON THE MACHINE.

31:07.230 --> 31:09.448
HEY.
HE'S FINE.
PUT YOUR HANDS ON THE MACHINE.

31:09.500 --> 31:12.321
SORRY --
HEY!
DOV: HE'S CLEAN.

31:12.370 --> 31:15.032
[ HANDCUFFS CLICK ]
GENE MacKENZIE, YOU'RE UNDER
ARREST FOR CHILD ABDUCT ION.

31:15.070 --> 31:16.469
WE'RE GONNA TAKE YOU
INTO THE STATION,

31:16.500 --> 31:18.559
AND YOU'RE GONNA TALK
TO A DETECTIVE.

31:24.580 --> 31:27.208
WE WERE TOGETHER
FOR A FEW MONTHS --

31:27.250 --> 31:29.343
RIGHT AFTER
DIAZ DUMPED HER.

31:33.290 --> 31:35.485
TOOK ME A WHILE TO FIGURE OUT
THE TIMING

31:35.520 --> 31:37.988
BEFORE I REALIZED
THAT CHRISTIAN WAS MINE.

31:38.030 --> 31:40.590
I MEAN...

31:40.630 --> 31:44.498
HE LOOKS JUST LIKE I DID
AT THAT AGE.

31:44.530 --> 31:46.464
I COULD SHOW YOU
BABY PICTURES.

31:46.500 --> 31:48.934
WHY DIDN'T YOU GET
A PATERNITY TEST?

31:48.970 --> 31:50.961
DENISE WOULDN'T GO FOR IT.

31:53.370 --> 31:56.032
AND I'D NEVER
GET CUSTODY ANYWAY.

31:56.080 --> 31:58.503
BECAUSE OF YOUR RECORD.

31:58.550 --> 32:01.075
BECAUSE I HIT HER.

32:01.120 --> 32:02.473
ONCE.

32:02.520 --> 32:04.943
WHEN WE WERE TOGETHER.

32:04.990 --> 32:10.155
BUT, LOOK, I HAVEN'T BEEN
IN ANY TROUBLE SINCE THEN.

32:10.190 --> 32:13.956
YOU KNOW,
I-I WORK REALLY HARD.

32:14.000 --> 32:15.524
I VOLUNTEER.

32:15.560 --> 32:17.699
I MEAN, SHE SIGNED
CHRISTIAN UP FOR SOCCER

32:17.730 --> 32:19.459
SO I COULD SEE HIM
ONCE A WEEK.

32:19.500 --> 32:21.968
WELL, IT SOUNDS LIKE YOU HAD
AN AGREEMENT REGARDING CUSTODY.

32:22.000 --> 32:24.139
WE DID, BUT THEN...

32:24.170 --> 32:27.207
DIAZ SHOWS UP,
AND THAT'S IT.

32:27.240 --> 32:28.639
SHE PULLS CHRISTIAN
OUT OF SOCCER.

32:28.680 --> 32:30.238
SHE WON'T LET ME
SEE HIM ANYMORE.

32:30.280 --> 32:31.599
SHE WON'T ANSWER
MY PHONE CALLS.

32:31.650 --> 32:35.074
SHE'S PRETENDING
LIKE I DON'T EXIST.

32:35.120 --> 32:38.487
SO, THIS MORNING,
I DROVE OVER THERE.

32:38.520 --> 32:40.681
I WAS JUST GONNA
LAY IT ALL OUT,

32:40.720 --> 32:42.153
TELL DIAZ THE TRUTH.

32:45.590 --> 32:47.251
[ SIGHS ]

32:47.290 --> 32:49.258
THEY WERE PULLING
OUT OF THE DRIVEWAY.

32:49.300 --> 32:51.097
SO YOU FOLLOWED THEM.

32:51.130 --> 32:52.495
A FEW HOURS LATER,

32:52.530 --> 32:56.091
I'M SITTING THERE
WATCHING MY SON...

32:56.140 --> 32:57.164
[ SIGHS ]

32:57.200 --> 33:01.102
...IN SOME PARK WITH PEOPLE
I'VE NEVER SEEN BEFORE.

33:01.140 --> 33:03.074
I COULDN'T HANDLE IT.

33:03.110 --> 33:07.342
SHE NEVER EVEN GAVE ME A CHANCE
TO BE HIS DAD.

33:10.550 --> 33:13.087
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

33:13.120 --> 33:16.180
HEY.

33:16.220 --> 33:18.484
UH, DO YOU KNOW
IF CHRIS IS STILL AROUND?

33:18.530 --> 33:22.751
UH, HE AND DENISE TOOK CHRISTIAN
BACK TO THE APARTMENT.

33:22.800 --> 33:24.495
UH, HAVE YOU SEEN DOV?

33:24.530 --> 33:27.294
I DON'T REALLY KEEP TABS
ON YOUR BOYFRIEND.

33:27.330 --> 33:30.663
OKAY, WELL, DO YOU KNOW
IF HE'S GONE HOME?

33:30.700 --> 33:32.167
BECAUSE...

33:32.210 --> 33:33.461
CHLOE, SEE THIS?

33:33.510 --> 33:35.034
I HAVE A LOT OF FORENSIC
BLAH-BLAH-BLAH

33:35.080 --> 33:36.206
THAT I HAVE TO ADD
TO MY NOTES.

33:36.240 --> 33:38.606
I HAVE TO BE SOMEWHERE
IN AN HOUR,

33:38.650 --> 33:40.800
SO IF YOU DON'T MIND,
CAN YOU JUST...

33:40.850 --> 33:42.715
GO BE SOMEWHERE ELSE,
PLEASE?

33:42.750 --> 33:45.048
YEAH, OKAY.

33:45.090 --> 33:46.148
WELL, WHEN YOU DO GO HOME,

33:46.190 --> 33:48.408
DO YOU THINK YOU COULD JUST
DROP THIS OFF FOR ME?

33:48.460 --> 33:50.348
DO I LOOK LIKE A FedEX BOX
TO YOU, CHLOE?

33:50.390 --> 33:53.484
THE OLD ONE'S GONNA BE
IN EVIDENCE FOR A WHILE, SO...

33:53.530 --> 33:56.090
WHERE DID YOU GET THAT?

33:56.130 --> 34:00.123
I WENT BY EMERSON TOYS,
'CAUSE I THOUGHT IT MIGHT HELP.

34:00.170 --> 34:03.094
YOU KNOW, AFTER A DAY LIKE
CHRISTIAN'S HAD TODAY, SO...

34:03.140 --> 34:04.562
ANYWAYS, UM,
COULD YOU JUST...

34:04.610 --> 34:06.237
YEAH, SURE.
...GIVE THAT TO CHRIS?

34:06.270 --> 34:07.237
OKAY. THAN KS.

34:07.270 --> 34:08.498
HEY.

34:08.540 --> 34:10.371
YEAH?

34:10.410 --> 34:12.503
YOU'RE VERY WIDE OPEN
AND BRIGHT-EYED.

34:12.550 --> 34:15.371
IT'S KIND OF LIKE YOU BELONG
IN "THE SOUND OF MUSIC."

34:15.420 --> 34:17.638
WHAT THAT MEANS, CHLOE,

34:17.680 --> 34:19.409
IS THAT YOU'RE NOT AFRAID
TO BE YOURSELF,

34:19.450 --> 34:20.781
AND IT DRIVES ME CRAZY.

34:23.260 --> 34:25.285
BECAUSE I...

34:25.330 --> 34:28.219
I GET IT, GAIL.

34:28.260 --> 34:29.158
APOLOGY ACCEPTED.

34:29.200 --> 34:32.363
OH, YEAH, UM, ACTUALLY,
I'M NOT APOLOGIZING.

34:32.400 --> 34:36.166
YES, YOU ARE.
HAVE A GOOD NIGHT, GAIL.

34:38.540 --> 34:44.240
[ RADIO CHATTER,
CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

34:44.280 --> 34:46.578
TOUGH DAY?
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:46.610 --> 34:48.214
YOU SHOULD SEE
THE OTHER GUY.

34:48.250 --> 34:49.342
YEAH.

34:49.380 --> 34:50.517
[ OBJECTS THUD LIGHTLY ON DESK ]

34:50.550 --> 34:52.347
LOOK, OLIVER,
ABOUT THIS MORNING, I...

34:52.390 --> 34:54.585
YOU KNOW, WE DON'T HAVE
TO DO THIS, SAM.

34:54.620 --> 34:56.281
I TRAINED THEM.

34:56.320 --> 34:57.355
OKAY.

34:57.390 --> 34:59.255
ACTUALLY,
I TRAINED THEM, TOO,

34:59.290 --> 35:02.191
SO...DON'T STEP ON MY TOES
WHEN WE'RE AROUND THEM.

35:02.230 --> 35:04.266
COOL?

35:04.300 --> 35:06.461
YOU'RE GONNA LOOK GOOD
IN A WHITE SHIRT ONE DAY.

35:06.500 --> 35:07.626
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:07.670 --> 35:09.592
THAT'S WHAT HAPPENS
WHEN I'M IN CHARGE.

35:09.640 --> 35:12.131
HEY, EVERYBODY WAS EXACTLY
WHERE THEY NEEDED TO BE

35:12.170 --> 35:13.205
TO GET THE JOB DONE.

35:13.240 --> 35:15.208
THAT'S WHAT HAPPENS
WHEN YOU'RE IN CHARGE.

35:18.180 --> 35:19.772
SEE YOU TOMORROW.

35:19.810 --> 35:22.347
SEE YOU, BROTHER.

35:35.800 --> 35:37.324
IS IT LEO?

35:38.830 --> 35:40.923
IS THAT THE REASON THAT YOU
WON'T DATE MY BROTHER?

35:40.970 --> 35:44.599
[ SIGHS ]

35:44.640 --> 35:48.269
I'M EXHAUSTED, GAIL.

35:48.310 --> 35:50.574
CAN WE TALK ABOUT THIS
TOMORROW?

35:50.610 --> 35:51.770
OR NEVER?

35:51.810 --> 35:55.519
NO, IT'S JUST I'M TRYING TO SAY
THAT I GET IT.

35:55.550 --> 35:58.189
I MEAN, THINGS MUST BE A HELL
OF A LOT MORE COMPLICATED

35:58.220 --> 36:00.279
WHEN YOU HAVE A KID.

36:00.320 --> 36:01.878
I LIKE STEVE.

36:03.720 --> 36:06.951
BUT I JUST FIGURED OUT HOW TO
MAKE MY LIFE WORK AGAIN.

36:06.990 --> 36:09.424
I CAN'T THROW DATING
INTO THE MIX.

36:09.460 --> 36:11.792
YEAH, BUT I'M GOING ON
A DIFFERENT DATE EVERY NIGHT,

36:11.830 --> 36:13.969
MAKING YOU PICK OUT
MY STUPID OUTFITS.

36:14.000 --> 36:15.490
WHICH I REALLY DON'T MIND.

36:15.540 --> 36:17.792
BESIDES, EVERYONE DESERVES
TO BE HAPPY, GAIL.

36:17.840 --> 36:19.307
EVEN YOU.

36:23.910 --> 36:26.401
[ KEYPAD CLICKING ]

36:26.450 --> 36:29.374
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

36:29.420 --> 36:31.445
HEY.

36:31.490 --> 36:33.481
WHAT ARE YOU DOING TONIGHT?

36:33.520 --> 36:35.579
DO YOU THINK CHRIS
IS GONNA BE OKAY?

36:35.620 --> 36:37.212
[ SIGHS ]
I DON'T KNOW.

36:37.260 --> 36:38.488
I DON'T THINK HE KNOWS.

36:38.530 --> 36:39.656
AND WHAT DO YOU DO

36:39.690 --> 36:42.227
WHEN A BOMB LIKE THAT GETS
DROPPED ON YOUR LIFE, YOU KNOW?

36:42.260 --> 36:45.525
YEAH, I'M GLAD I TOLD FRANK
ABOUT US.

36:45.570 --> 36:48.892
I WANT US TO ALWAYS BE HONEST
WITH EACH OTHER --

36:48.940 --> 36:50.396
ABOUT EVERYTHING.

36:50.440 --> 36:51.964
ME TOO.

37:04.390 --> 37:06.312
DID HE FINALLY
FALL ASLEEP?

37:08.790 --> 37:11.350
CHRIS...

37:11.390 --> 37:14.518
THANK YOU FOR TODAY.
YOU WERE AMAZING.

37:15.600 --> 37:16.953
NOW THAT CHRISTIAN'S SAFE,

37:17.000 --> 37:18.922
WE CAN -- WE CAN GO HOME
AND...

37:18.970 --> 37:20.426
PUT ALL THIS BEHIND US.

37:20.470 --> 37:24.509
I LEFT MY APARTMENT...

37:24.540 --> 37:26.929
MY JOB...

37:26.970 --> 37:29.473
AND MY FRIENDS...

37:29.510 --> 37:30.932
BECAUSE OF YOU.

37:30.980 --> 37:33.278
WELL, WE CAN --
WE CAN MOVE BACK.

37:33.310 --> 37:36.518
WE CAN DO WHATEVER YOU WANT
AS LONG AS WE'RE A FAMILY.

37:36.550 --> 37:37.949
BUT WE'RE NOT A FAMILY.

37:37.980 --> 37:41.017
AND CHRISTIAN [SIGHS]

37:41.050 --> 37:45.419
HOW COULD YOU...LET ME THINK
THAT I WAS HIS DAD?

37:45.460 --> 37:47.655
HOW C-- [SIGHS]

37:47.690 --> 37:49.829
HOW COULD YOU GIVE HIM
TO ME...

37:49.860 --> 37:52.363
AND KNOW HE WASN'T MINE?

37:52.400 --> 37:53.560
WELL, I DIDN'T KNOW
FOR SURE.

37:53.600 --> 37:54.635
WELL, YOU SHOULD HAVE
MADE SURE

37:54.670 --> 37:56.069
BEFORE YOU SHOWED UP HERE
AND YOU RUINED MY LIFE.

37:56.100 --> 37:57.897
I WANTED HIM
TO BE YOURS!
THAT IS N--

37:57.940 --> 37:59.498
THAT'S NOT GOOD ENOUGH.

37:59.540 --> 38:02.304
EVERYTHING
THAT HAPPENED TODAY,

38:02.340 --> 38:06.948
IN MY HEART,
HE STILL FEELS LIKE MY SON.

38:06.980 --> 38:09.574
I LOOK AT HIM,
AND I SEE MY SON.

38:09.620 --> 38:11.315
MINE!

38:13.850 --> 38:15.784
WHAT AM I
SUPPOSED TO DO NOW?

38:15.820 --> 38:18.482
I'M SO SORRY.
I'M SO SORRY, CHRIS.

38:18.530 --> 38:21.852
[ DAVE THOMAS JUNIOR'S
"3 WISHES" PLAYS ]

38:30.470 --> 38:31.767
HEY.

38:31.810 --> 38:33.368
WHAT'S GOING ON?

38:33.410 --> 38:34.775
I JUST WANTED
TO CHECK IN ON YOU

38:34.810 --> 38:36.107
AND MAKE SURE
YOU'RE ALL RIGHT.

38:36.140 --> 38:37.368
WELL [SIGHS]

38:37.410 --> 38:39.071
I'VE HAD BETTER DAYS.

38:39.110 --> 38:40.338
[ DOOR UNLOCKS ]

38:40.380 --> 38:42.416
SO HAVE YOU.

38:42.450 --> 38:44.441
WANT TO COME IN?
FOR A DRINK OR SOMETHING?

38:44.490 --> 38:46.640
I ALSO WANTED TO TELL YOU
I THINK YOU'RE RIGHT.

38:46.690 --> 38:48.089
ABOUT WHAT?

38:48.120 --> 38:50.611
ABOUT...US.

38:50.660 --> 38:52.548
MM.
YOU'RE RIGHT...

38:52.590 --> 38:53.557
ABOUT ALL THE PROBLEMS.

38:53.590 --> 38:54.898
I DID JUST BREAK UP
WITH GAIL.

38:54.930 --> 38:55.726
WE WORK TOGETHER.

38:55.760 --> 38:57.398
YOU AND ME,
YOU KNOW, WE'RE FRIENDS.

38:57.430 --> 38:58.692
DON'T WANT
TO JEOPARDIZE THAT.

38:58.730 --> 39:01.437
NOPE.

39:01.470 --> 39:02.937
[ KEYS JINGLE ]

39:02.970 --> 39:06.030
ALL THAT'S TRUE.
THE THING IS, I DON'T CARE.

39:06.070 --> 39:09.836
YOU'RE WORTH IT.
YOU'RE THE MOST...

39:09.880 --> 39:11.370
AMAZING PERSON
I'VE EVER MET.

39:11.410 --> 39:13.446
AND THE FACT THAT
YOU'VE THOUGHT THIS THROUGH

39:13.480 --> 39:15.016
MEANS I'VE GOT
A FIGHTING CHANCE.

39:15.050 --> 39:18.383
SO I'LL WAIT.

39:18.420 --> 39:21.082
HOWEVER LONG THAT TAKES.

39:23.990 --> 39:26.652
**

39:26.690 --> 39:28.555
OHH.

39:28.600 --> 39:29.692
OH.

39:29.730 --> 39:30.856
* YOU KNOW HOW THE RULES GO

39:30.900 --> 39:33.494
ALSO, I FORGOT
TO GIVE YOU THIS.

39:33.530 --> 39:35.395
I, UH...
* YOU CAN'T WISH
FOR WORLD PEACE *

39:35.440 --> 39:37.761
I PICKED IT UP
AT THE HOSPITAL.

39:37.800 --> 39:39.563
THANK YOU.
PROBABLY SHOULD HAVE STARTED
WITH THAT,

39:39.610 --> 39:41.931
'CAUSE NOW
IT'S SUPER AWKWARD.

39:41.980 --> 39:43.971
* ...ANYONE
[ CHUCKLES ]

39:44.010 --> 39:46.547
* AND WE'RE LETTING
OLD FRIENDS BE *

39:46.580 --> 39:51.449
* YOU CAN'T WISH
FOR MORE WISHES *

39:51.490 --> 39:55.950
* BUT THAT DON'T BOTHER ME

39:55.990 --> 40:00.427
* 'CAUSE IF I HAD
THREE WISHES *

40:00.460 --> 40:06.797
* YOU WOULD BE ALL THREE

40:09.800 --> 40:13.736
* IF YOU HAD THREE WISHES

40:13.770 --> 40:16.705
* DO YOU KNOW WHAT THEY'D BE?

40:16.740 --> 40:18.207
COME ON.
IT'S CATHARTIC.

40:18.240 --> 40:20.071
ESPECIALLY AFTER A DAY
LIKE TODAY.

40:20.110 --> 40:22.772
I DON'T REALLY, LIKE,
DO SPORTS.

40:22.820 --> 40:26.586
IT'S NOT GONNA KILL YOU
TO TRY SOMETHING NEW.

40:26.620 --> 40:30.511
* IF I HAD THREE WISHES
[ MACHINE BEEPS ]

40:30.560 --> 40:32.118
AAH! [ LAUGHS ]

40:32.160 --> 40:34.958
* TELL YOU WHAT THEY'D BE

40:35.000 --> 40:36.092
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

40:36.130 --> 40:37.222
SORRY.

40:37.260 --> 40:41.560
ACTUALLY, IT MIGHT KILL YOU.
[ LAUGHS ]

40:41.600 --> 40:44.808
[ Laughing ] I'M SORRY.
* YOU WOULD BE ALL THREE

40:44.840 --> 40:46.660
I FEEL SO HUMILIATED.

40:46.710 --> 40:49.577
I TOLD YOU,
I DON'T LIKE SPORTS!

40:49.610 --> 40:52.545
AND I'M LEAVING.

40:52.580 --> 40:55.617
**

40:59.750 --> 41:01.650
HEY, IT'S ME.

41:01.690 --> 41:03.055
I'M LEAVING NOW.

41:03.090 --> 41:05.524
I'LL, UH, I'LL SEE YOU SOON.

41:12.830 --> 41:16.869
* I COULD SAY I WANT TO FLY

41:16.900 --> 41:21.269
* BUT THAT WOULD GET OLD
AFTER A WHILE *

41:21.310 --> 41:25.679
* A MILLION THINGS
THAT I COULD DO *

41:25.710 --> 41:30.647
* BUT THEY'D MEAN NOTHING
WITHOUT YOU *

41:30.680 --> 41:34.241
* SO I CAN'T THINK
OF ANYTHING *

41:37.560 --> 41:42.293
* IF YOU HAD THREE WISHES
IT'S -- IT'S FINE.

41:42.330 --> 41:44.195
[ CLATTER ]
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.
IT'S FINE.

41:44.230 --> 41:46.869
* YOU KNOW WHAT THEY'D BE

41:46.900 --> 41:51.132
* BUT ONE GETS SAVED
FOR A RAINY DAY *
[ Laughing ] OH, MY GOD.

41:51.170 --> 41:53.058
[ CLATTER, CRASH ]

41:53.110 --> 41:55.931
* FOR SOMEONE MORE IN NEED
I DON'T CARE.

41:55.980 --> 42:00.007
* IF I HAD THREE WISHES

42:00.050 --> 42:02.314
* I TELL YOU WHAT THEY'D BE

42:02.350 --> 42:04.716
OH! [ LAUGHS ]

42:04.750 --> 42:09.119
* IF I HAD THREE WISHES

42:09.160 --> 42:12.857
* YOU WOULD BE

42:12.890 --> 42:17.827
* ALL THREE
